A video of a Malcolm X dishing out R100 notes to bus
passengers has surfaced on social media. Malcolm X, also known as a friend of the homeless, the
hungry and the needy, surprised passengers with cash. HE IS OFTEN SEEN ON THE STREETS GIVING COMFORT TO THOSE
WHO NEED IT. WATCH: BLESSER WITH A DIFFERENCE! The video shows him stopping a bus which was about to
drive off. As soon as he gets on the bus, he starts giving out R100
notes. When one passenger asks what is it for, the he replies
that "it's for lunch". All people in the bus, including the driver received R100
notes. It's not clear when and where the video was taken.